# UPDATE (PUT) a note by id - REST Client examples
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001

### Update note with id - example 1
@id = 69500d7ef71f7a542288ee14
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/notes/{{id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Updated note content",
  "important": true
}

### Update another id - example 2
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/notes/69500d7ef71f7a542288ee15
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "This note is now very important!",
  "important": true
}

### Update only content, keep important as is
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/notes/69500d7ef71f7a542288ee14
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Changed content only",
  "important": false
}

# cURL equivalent (run in terminal):
# curl -i -X PUT http://localhost:3001/api/notes/69500d7ef71f7a542288ee14 \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"content":"Updated content","important":true}'

# How it works:
# 1. The route is /api/notes/{id} with PUT method
# 2. Send JSON body with fields to update: content, important
# 3. Server returns updated note object with new data
# 4. Use { new: true } to return the updated document (not the old one)
